President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Judge Beth Bloom, Paul G. Byron, Judge Darrin P. Gayles, and Judge Carlos Eduardo Mendoza to serve on the United States District Courts. These individuals have demonstrated a commitment to public service throughout their careers. Judge Beth Bloom has served as a Circuit Judge in Florida since 2010. Paul G. Byron is a partner at a law firm and has experience in civil litigation. Judge Darrin P. Gayles has served as a Circuit Judge in Florida since 2011. Judge Carlos Eduardo Mendoza has served as a Circuit Judge in Florida since 2011 and has prior experience as an Assistant City Attorney. Judge Mendoza also served in the United States Marine Corps.